#!ek9
<?-
  Literal Validation Fuzz Test: Duration - Empty Duration
  Tests if EK9 catches empty duration literal (P with no components) at compile time.

  Expected: Should fail (duration must have at least one component like P1Y or PT1H)
  Actual: Compiles successfully, becomes unset at runtime
-?>
defines module fuzz.literal.duration.empty
  defines program
    Test()
      d <- P
      stdout <- Stdout()
      if d?
        stdout.println("Set")
//EOF
